Delta hydraulic systems were targeted during the Charter Wars because flooding could be weaponized: releasing upstream water at strategic times could destroy settlements that could not be taken by direct assault.
Deltari communities survived Charter Wars period disruption by using their hydraulic knowledge to anticipate and partially redirect weaponized flooding.
